sentences: Matt Hyde (born June 19, 1964) is an American producer, engineer, mixer and musician.
From 1982 to 1985 he attended Berklee College of Music in Boston.
While still at Berklee in 1984, he obtained an internship at Pyramid Recording Studio in Boston.
When he returned to the U.S., he began working at recording studios, first in Boston and from 1989 in Los Angeles.
In 2006, Hyde was recognized for engineering Jonny Lang's album Turn Around, which won a Grammy in the Best Rock or Rap Gospel category.
